{{Top|leg}}
'''Blastonecrosis''' was a highly lethal disease. Symptoms included fatigue and loss of appetite. Blastonecrosis could be masked by the consumption of [[lotiramine]], which hid the tracer enzymes marking the disease's presence in the body. In addition to causing severe bacta allergies in all patients, the purposely contaminated [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] from [[Lot ZX1449F]] caused roughly two percent of those exposed to contract blastonecrosis. In these cases, blastonecrosis was incurable, as bacta was the only effective treatment for the disease.

